                <p class="text-sm md:text-base">Dr. Cherson is a native New Yorker. He received his BA in History with honors from Queens College of the City University of New York. He attended medical school at the New York College of Osteopathic Medicine of The New York Institute of Technology and completed his internship at Peninsula Hospital Center in Queens, New York. Dr. Cherson then completed a residency in emergency medicine at St. Barnabas Hospital Bronx, NY and a fellowship in prehospital care with the Fire Department City of New York. Dr. Cherson received his Masters Degree in Health Care Administration from Kaplan University.<br><br>
